data.name: Dutch Apple Pie

ingredients.name: apples
ingredients.quantity: 6 cups, peeled and sliced (about 6 medium apples)

data.quickTastyDescription: A classic dessert with a buttery crust, sweet apple filling, and a crumbly topping that’s simply irresistible!
detailedCookingInstructions: Roll out the pie crust and fit it into a 9-inch pie pan.
In a large bowl, combine the sliced apples, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice, and flour. Toss until the apples are well coated.
Pour the apple mixture into the prepared pie crust, spreading it evenly.
In another bowl, mix together the cold butter, oats, flour, brown sugar, and salt until crumbly.
Sprinkle the crumb topping over the apples in the pie.
Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Then reduce the temperature to 350°F (175°C) and bake for an additional 30-40 minutes, until the apples are tender and the crust is golden brown.
Let the pie cool for at least 10 minutes before serving. Enjoy!
data.modifiersForBase: Dutch style with a crumb topping
